Nepal: Bus plunges into river, 20 killed 
9-3-2017 
At least 20 people were reportedly killed, and around 40 wounded when a bus packed to its capacity fell 200 metres into a river in Nepalâ€™s far west Jajarkot district on Thursday.

Police said the bus, that left district headquarters Khalanga in the morning , fell into Pasagarh river killing 13 on the spot, while at least another seven died in the hospital. 
